            counter = 0; // reset counter for next iteration of this if statement block after incrementing its count if not "The"
        }
    }// end while (in.good()) loop that reads lines from the file until EOF is reached. Note that we use "in.good()" as an if-statement condition, which will only execute this block of code when in.good() is true, which means there are still lines left to read from the input file. If in.good() returns false, then there are no more lines left to read from the input file, and we will not enter this block of code. This allows us to continue reading lines from the input file even if some lines have already been skipped because they contained an empty line or some other special characters that would cause in.good() to return false prematurely.

